The `isPrime` function checks if a given number `n` is prime. It returns `false` if `n` is less than or equal to 1 (since prime numbers are greater than 1). Otherwise, it iterates from 2 to the square root of `n` using a loop variable `i`, checking if `n` is divisible by any of these numbers. If it finds a divisor, it returns `false`. If it reaches the end of the loop without finding a divisor, it returns `true`.

